==English==

===Etymology===
From the {{etyl|el}} [[αντί]] ''anti'' "against" + [[νόμος]] ''nomos'' “custom, law”.

===Noun===
'''antinomianism'''

# {{Christianity}} a belief that the [[Law]] was completely abrogated by [[Jesus]] so that it has no meaning for the present day [[Christian]] believer which is perceived by most Christians as [[heretical]].
# {{Judaism}} opposition to the [[Torah]].


